# pyenv
#   For a library or app, you might want to share your .python-version if you
#   use pyenv and want other developers to use the same Python version
#.python-version

# pipenv
#   According to Pipfile.lock, it is recommended to include Pipfile.lock in version control.
#   However, in case of collaboration, it might be better to exclude it.
#   https://pipenv.pypa.io/en/latest/advanced/#pipfile-vs-setup-py
#Pipfile.lock

# poetry
#   Similar to Pipenv, poetry.lock can be include in version control or excluded.
#   https://python-poetry.org/docs/basic-usage/#commit-your-poetrylock-file-to-version-control
#poetry.lock

# pdm
#   Similar to Pipenv and Poetry, pdm.lock can be include in version control or excluded.
#   https://pdm.fming.dev/#commit-your-pdmlock-file-to-version-control
#.pdm.toml
#.pdm-python
#.pdm-build/

# PEP 582; used by e.g. github.com/lincolnloop/layman and github.com/pdm-project/pdm
__pypackages__/

